# Services Structure

The application is organized into multiple service modules:

## Core Services

- **Database Service**: [src/services/database](mdc:src/services/database) - Database connection and operations
- **Storage Service**: [src/services/storage.js](mdc:src/services/storage.js) - Google Cloud Storage operations
- **Email Service**: [src/services/email](mdc:src/services/email) - SendGrid integration for communications
- **Encryption Service**: [src/services/encryption.js](mdc:src/services/encryption.js) - Data security and encryption
- **OpenAI Service**: [src/services/openai.js](mdc:src/services/openai.js) - AI integration for appraisals
- **PubSub Service**: [src/services/pubsub](mdc:src/services/pubsub) - Messaging and event handling
- **Sheets Service**: [src/services/sheets](mdc:src/services/sheets) - Google Sheets integration
- **Report Composer**: [src/services/reportComposer.js](mdc:src/services/reportComposer.js) - Generates appraisal reports

## Message Handling

- **Message Handler**: [src/services/message/handler.js](mdc:src/services/message/handler.js) - Processes incoming messages

## Initialization

All services are initialized in [index.js](mdc:index.js), which loads necessary credentials and configures each service before starting the application.
